      "text": "Diff confirmed"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.0,
      "end": 59.95,
      "text": "Same rain"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.0,
      "end": 61.95,
      "text": "Different line"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.0,
      "end": 64.95,
      "text": "Not hidden in the frame"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.0,
      "end": 67.95,
      "text": "What changes the message"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.0,
      "end": 71.95,
      "text": "without changing the rain"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.0,
      "end": 74.95,
      "text": "The loudest line"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.0,
      "end": 101.95,
      "text": "And I witnessed firsthand which methods governments use to suppress our freedoms and to take away our basic rights. I've seen all the tricks. And the thing that bothers me most today is that some of the same tricks that have been employed by authoritarian regimes in places like Russia or China and Iran, are now being also used in some Western countries. You say something politically incorrect online, you may end up being fined or spend some time in prison."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.0,
      "end": 134.95,
      "text": "So now people are afraid to use their real identities. People stop using their real names when they make comments online. And the European Commission is pushing for a new measure. A measure to require that all social media users present their IDs before they can access social media sites. The official justification is child protection. They want to ban social media services for everybody under 16, and for that, they need people to verify their age by presenting their ID."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.0,
      "end": 136.95,
      "text": "Motive unknown"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.0,
      "end": 138.95,
      "text": "Diff confirmed"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.0,
      "end": 140.95,
      "text": "Diff confirmed"
    },
    {
      "start": 141.0,
      "end": 143.95,
      "text": "Not hidden in the frame"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.0,
      "end": 146.95,
      "text": "What changes the message"
    },
    {
      "start": 147.0,
      "end": 152.95,
      "text": "But what will happen if social media sites are banned for teenagers? Will it bring harm or good?"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.0,
      "end": 155.95,
      "text": "Actually, we know the answer to this question."
    },
    {
      "start": 156.0,
      "end": 160.0,
      "text": "Why? Because it has already been tried."
    }
  ],
  "10": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.95,
      "text": "One"
    },
    {
      "start": 2.0,
      "end": 3.95,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 4.0,
      "end": 5.95,
      "text": "glowing screen"
    },
    {
      "start": 6.0,
      "end": 7.95,
      "text": "verify the ID"
    },
    {
      "start": 8.0,
      "end": 10.95,
      "text": "They say it's for the youth they say it's the key"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.0,
      "end": 13.95,
      "text": "But you pull out the passport and what do they take"
    },
    {
      "start": 14.0,
      "end": 16.95,
      "text": "Every little secret for a database sake"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.0,
      "end": 18.95,
      "text": "A digital checkpoint"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.0,
      "end": 20.95,
      "text": "A heavy glass toll"
    },
    {
      "start": 21.0,
      "end": 22.95,
      "text": "You just want access"
    },
    {
      "start": 23.0,
      "end": 24.95,
      "text": "They want the whole soul"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.0,
      "end": 25.95,
      "text": "Old enough?"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.0,
      "end": 26.95,
      "text": "Yes"
    },
    {
      "start": 27.0,
      "end": 27.95,
      "text": "Full name?"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.0,
      "end": 28.95,
      "text": "No"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.0,
      "end": 29.95,
      "text": "No"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 30.95,
      "text": "Home address?"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.0,
      "end": 31.95,
      "text": "No"
    },
    {
      "start": 32.0,
      "end": 32.95,
      "text": "Face scan?"
    },
    {
      "start": 33.0,
      "end": 34.95,
      "text": "No"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.0,
      "end": 36.95,
      "text": "One bit of truth"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.0,
      "end": 39.95,
      "text": "is all they need to know"
    },
    {
      "start": 40.0,
      "end": 41.95,
      "text": "Not the number not the photo"
    },
    {
      "start": 42.0,
      "end": 43.95,
      "text": "not the place you go"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.0,
      "end": 45.95,
      "text": "Protect the kids"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.0,
      "end": 47.95,
      "text": "don't build a file"
    },
    {
      "start": 48.0,
      "end": 50.95,
      "text": "Safety shouldn't mean a database trial"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.0,
      "end": 52.95,
      "text": "prove the age"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.0,
      "end": 54.95,
      "text": "Not identity"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.0,
      "end": 55.95,
      "text": "lock the door"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.0,
      "end": 57.95,
      "text": "door"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.0,
      "end": 59.95,
      "text": "keep the dignity"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.0,
      "end": 63.95,
      "text": "So Russia banned Telegram"
    },
    {
      "start": 64.0,
      "end": 66.95,
      "text": "The largest social media platform at the time"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.0,
      "end": 69.95,
      "text": "for all its citizens"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.0,
      "end": 75.95,
      "text": "because we refused to comply with their demands for mass surveillance and censorship"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.0,
      "end": 82.95,
      "text": "However, 95% of Russian teenagers still use Telegram every month"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.0,
      "end": 87.95,
      "text": "How? They use VPNs. They bypass the entire thing."
    },
    {
      "start": 88.0,
      "end": 93.95,
      "text": "And there's very little you can do with VPNs. Russia is trying very hard."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.0,
      "end": 101.95,
      "text": "They have invested billions in trying to fight VPNs. They're banning hundreds of VPNs every month."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.0,
      "end": 111.95,
      "text": "using IP addresses and traffic patterns. They even installed surveillance hardware into every data center of every internet provider in the country"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.0,
      "end": 116.0,
      "text": "Trying to monitor all the traffic and trying to prevent people from using VPNs. And they failed. Despite all this effort, they failed."
    }
  ],
  "11": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.95,
      "text": "Read the rain"
    },
    {
      "start": 6.0,
      "end": 8.95,
      "text": "Not what is written"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.0,
      "end": 10.95,
      "text": "How it falls"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.0,
      "end": 12.95,
      "text": "Appearance"
    },
    {
      "start": 13.0,
      "end": 16.95,
      "text": "Rhythm"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.0,
      "end": 20.95,
      "text": "Why is the grid clean and broken at 86?"
    },
    {
      "start": 21.0,
      "end": 23.95,
      "text": "What is frame 347 carrying?"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.0,
      "end": 29.95,
      "text": "A rename scar?"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 32.95,
      "text": "Look at the \"@\" signs placed with precision"
    },
    {
      "start": 33.0,
      "end": 34.95,
      "text": "The plus in an address"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.0,
      "end": 39.95,
      "text": "In the column where rhythm stops obeying"
    },
    {
      "start": 40.0,
      "end": 44.95,
      "text": "This may not be an email address"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.0,
      "end": 51.95,
      "text": "It may be a hint"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.0,
      "end": 53.95,
      "text": "But a hand"
    },
    {
      "start": 54.0,
      "end": 58.95,
      "text": "Also leaves a trace"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.0,
      "end": 73.95,
      "text": "Read the fall, read the grid, we read the rain, now read how it falls"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.0,
      "end": 78.0,
      "text": "What message is not written, but timed?"
    }
  ],
  "12": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.95,
      "text": "15 years ago, when I was still running VK, the largest social network in Russia at the time"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.0,
      "end": 12.95,
      "text": "We started to receive weird data requests from, from the Russian police."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.0,
      "end": 19.95,
      "text": "Now back then VK actually disclosed, in some cases, contents of private messages."
    },
    {
      "start": 20.0,
      "end": 29.95,
      "text": "Unlike Telegram today, which doesn't disclose it ever. VK, back in the day, did that, provided there was an official justification."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 38.95,
      "text": "And we started to notice something weird. Something was off about this data request coming from the Russian police."
    },
    {
      "start": 39.0,
      "end": 43.95,
      "text": "We realized that, that people who were included in this investigations"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.0,
      "end": 48.95,
      "text": "had nothing to do with, with the crimes that were described there."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.0,
      "end": 53.95,
      "text": "So we started to investigate the investigators."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.0,
      "end": 58.95,
      "text": "And we came to a conclusion, to a conclusion pretty fast"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.0,
      "end": 62.95,
      "text": "that the police was corrupt."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.0,
      "end": 73.95,
      "text": "They were trying to access private messages of innocent people in order to then blackmail them and sell their private data to criminals."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.0,
      "end": 78.95,
      "text": "They used it for harassment and other things."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.0,
      "end": 91.95,
      "text": "So you could say ok, you had this traumatizing experience in Russia, but surely nothing of the kind can happen in the civilized West."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.0,
      "end": 93.95,
      "text": "Well, I have bad news for you."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.0,
      "end": 106.95,
      "text": "Last year a French tax official was caught stealing the financial data of people who held large amount of crypto assets and other wealth."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.0,
      "end": 119.95,
      "text": "So a French tax bureaucrat was selling personal financial data of French citizens to criminals."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.0,
      "end": 130.95,
      "text": "People getting tortured, harmed, harassed, humiliated."
    },
    {
      "start": 131.0,
      "end": 135.95,
      "text": "All because the government wanted too much data and failed to protect it."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.0,
      "end": 141.95,
      "text": "In the world of AI, if we give up our right to privacy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 142.0,
      "end": 149.95,
      "text": "you can be certain that every message that you send will be monitored, will be analyzed."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.0,
      "end": 154.0,
      "text": "The future can become much darker and more dystopian than the Soviet Union of the 80s."
    }
  ],
  "13": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 3.95,
      "text": "The lens feels nothing, mirroring the void"
    },
    {
      "start": 4.0,
      "end": 8.95,
      "text": "A cold glass eye, a living breath, unbuoyed"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.0,
      "end": 12.95,
      "text": "The dust upon the shutter is the proof"
    },
    {
      "start": 13.0,
      "end": 22.95,
      "text": "We brush against the ceiling, not the roof"
    },
    {
      "start": 23.0,
      "end": 25.95,
      "text": "We look for pupils, searching for a gaze"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.0,
      "end": 28.95,
      "text": "Lost in the labyrinth of a digital maze"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.0,
      "end": 31.95,
      "text": "But when the light fell dead at 90 degrees"
    },
    {
      "start": 32.0,
      "end": 34.95,
      "text": "We found the math that brings us to our knees"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.0,
      "end": 37.95,
      "text": "Old surveillance needed eyes to see"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.0,
      "end": 43.95,
      "text": "Now it's all code, no humanity"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.0,
      "end": 48.95,
      "text": "And so long as men die, liberty will never perish"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.0,
      "end": 51.95,
      "text": "A million echoes in the hive's domain"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.0,
      "end": 54.95,
      "text": "No reader needed to interpret pain"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.0,
      "end": 57.95,
      "text": "One logic gate, one reason, one decree"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.0,
      "end": 64.95,
      "text": "A pipeline built to drown the silent sea"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.0,
      "end": 67.95,
      "text": "Oh, lordy, lord, the wires have a soul"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.0,
      "end": 70.95,
      "text": "They're turning heartbeats into charcoal"
    },
    {
      "start": 71.0,
      "end": 73.95,
      "text": "The stutter in your perfect code"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.0,
      "end": 76.95,
      "text": "A wayward traveler on a pathless road"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.0,
      "end": 79.95,
      "text": "Every draft, every thought"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.0,
      "end": 85.95,
      "text": "Every idea will be caught"
    },
    {
      "start": 86.0,
      "end": 100.95,
      "text": "Don't give yourselves to these unnatural men - machine men with machine minds and machine hearts! You are not machines! You are not cattle! You are men! You have the love of humanity in your hearts!"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.0,
      "end": 103.95,
      "text": "So cast the net, let innocence be data"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.0,
      "end": 104.95,
      "text": "Cold and set"
    },
    {
      "start": 105.0,
      "end": 107.95,
      "text": "The machine needs no malice for the cage"
    },
    {
      "start": 108.0,
      "end": 110.95,
      "text": "It only needs a metric for the stage"
    },
    {
      "start": 111.0,
      "end": 113.95,
      "text": "Old surveillance needed eyes of blue"
    },
    {
      "start": 114.0,
      "end": 119.95,
      "text": "New surveillance needs the scale of you"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.0,
      "end": 126.95,
      "text": "But reads without a face"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.0,
      "end": 130.95,
      "text": "Without a face"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.0,
      "end": 148.95,
      "text": "You, the people have the power - the power to create machines. The power to create happiness! You, the people, have the power to make this life free and beautiful, to make this life a wonderful adventure. Let us use that power - let us all unite."
    },
    {
      "start": 149.0,
      "end": 153.0,
      "text": "Without a face"
    }
  ],
  "14": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.95,
      "text": "So we don't have this luxury"
    },
    {
      "start": 3.0,
      "end": 5.95,
      "text": "that the passengers of the Titanic had"
    },
    {
      "start": 6.0,
      "end": 7.95,
      "text": "we cannot afford"
    },
    {
      "start": 8.0,
      "end": 10.95,
      "text": "to have this ship sunk."
    },
    {
      "start": 11.0,
      "end": 14.95,
      "text": "See there is nowhere to escape."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.0,
      "end": 18.95,
      "text": "In the past dissidents from authoritarian countries"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.0,
      "end": 21.95,
      "text": "could flee to the West."
    },
    {
      "start": 22.0,
      "end": 25.95,
      "text": "But if the current trajectory continues"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.0,
      "end": 30.95,
      "text": "in a decade or two from now they will have hard time"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.0,
      "end": 36.95,
      "text": "trying to understand whether they have already left their repressive homeland"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.0,
      "end": 41.95,
      "text": "or they are just entering another open air prison."
    },
    {
      "start": 42.0,
      "end": 43.95,
      "text": "Now..."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.0,
      "end": 46.95,
      "text": "I hope it will not come to that."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.0,
      "end": 50.95,
      "text": "But we need to realize the gravity of the situation."
    },
    {
      "start": 51.0,
      "end": 52.95,
      "text": "We need to start acting."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.0,
      "end": 55.95,
      "text": "We don't have a backup plan."
    },
    {
      "start": 56.0,
      "end": 57.95,
      "text": "We don't have lifeboats."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.0,
      "end": 59.95,
      "text": "There is no second West."
    },
    {
      "start": 60.0,
      "end": 62.95,
      "text": "There is no backup civilization."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.0,
      "end": 66.95,
      "text": "For decades or centuries the West has been"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.0,
      "end": 70.95,
      "text": "a guiding star for everybody who loved freedom"
    },
    {
      "start": 71.0,
      "end": 74.95,
      "text": "and we need to preserve that."
    },
    {
      "start": 75.0,
      "end": 77.95,
      "text": "If the ship of Western freedom sinks"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.0,
      "end": 79.95,
      "text": "the rest of the world"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.0,
      "end": 82.95,
      "text": "is likely to follow."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.0,
      "end": 86.95,
      "text": "We will lose freedoms everywhere."
    },
    {
      "start": 87.0,
      "end": 88.95,
      "text": "So we cannot"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.0,
      "end": 90.95,
      "text": "let this happen."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.0,
      "end": 92.95,
      "text": "We cannot"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.0,
      "end": 94.95,
      "text": "let this ship"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.0,
      "end": 97.95,
      "text": "sink."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.0,
      "end": 100.95,
      "text": "The only way forward"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.0,
      "end": 103.95,
      "text": "is to fix this ship."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.0,
      "end": 107.95,
      "text": "Let's do that."
    },
    {
      "start": 108.0,
      "end": 112.95,
      "text": "There is no backup civilization."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.0,
      "end": 117.95,
      "text": "If there are no lifeboats"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.0,
      "end": 122.95,
      "text": "Privacy is not a setting."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.0,
      "end": 124.95,
      "text": "Privacy is maintenance"
    },
    {
      "start": 125.0,
      "end": 126.95,
      "text": "discipline"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.0,
      "end": 128.95,
      "text": "memory"
    },
    {
      "start": 129.0,
      "end": 130.95,
      "text": "archive"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.0,
      "end": 135.95,
      "text": "method"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.0,
      "end": 139.95,
      "text": "Open the archive"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.0,
      "end": 144.95,
      "text": "Inspect the hull"
    },
    {
      "start": 145.0,
      "end": 149.95,
      "text": "The only way forward is to fix this ship"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.0,
      "end": 152.95,
      "text": "No second deck"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.0,
      "end": 156.95,
      "text": "No alternative net"
    },
    {
      "start": 157.0,
      "end": 160.95,
      "text": "Only maintenance"
    },
    {
      "start": 161.0,
      "end": 164.95,
      "text": "What cannot be escaped"
    },
    {
      "start": 165.0,
      "end": 169.0,
      "text": "and therefore must be repaired."
    }
  ]
}